ny Central, state and local Income Tax liability or any other statutory levies &amp; duties etc. of the franchisee or of any person assigned by the franchisee. However, nothing contained herein shall prevent the Achanumber.com from deducting tax at source (TDS) as required by law and regulation from payments to the franchisee.</li><li>The franchisee accepts for all purposes that any brand names, logos, trademarks and identifying slogans affixed by the Achanumber.com whether registered or not, constitute the exclusive property of the Achanumber.com and cannot be used except in connection with the promotion and sale of the services of the Achanumber.com.</li><li>In the event of termination of this Agreement, howsoever caused, the franchisee's right to use such trademarks, logos shall cease with immediate effect. The franchisee agrees not to attach any additional trademarks, logos or trade designations to any services of the Achanumber.com thereafter.</li><li>The franchisee will not publish, nor cause to be published, any advertising, or making any representations oral or written, which might confuse, mislead or deceive the public or which are detrimental to the name, trademarks, goodwill or reputation of the Achanumber.com.</li><li>The Achanumber.com shall be vested with the sole discretion to amend, review, suspend, cancel, change or extend the scope and ambit of the Achanumber.com services.</li><li>The Achanumber.com has the right to terminate this agreement forthwith in case it comes to conclusion that the franchisee has violated any of the clauses of the agreement. The decision of the Achanumber.com will be final in this regard.</li><li>All the franchisee's rights under this Agreement shall cease and no payment will be made out whatsoever shall be due to the franchisee and in that case the franchisee shall not claim for loss of goodwill, anticipated profits and any other claims or losses in respect of such termination. The franchisee hereby waives any claim to receive any compensation as a result of the termination of this Agreement.</li><li>Any sums payable under this Agreement and which are unpaid by the franchisee on the date of termination, shall forthwith become due and payable by the franchisee along with bank interest as applicable till the said amount is paid to the Achanumber.com.</li><li>Damages: In the event of termination of this agreement consequent upon breach of any of the terms of this agreement or surrender of franchisee ship at its own, will of the franchisee, damages to the extent of loss determined by the Achanumber.com shall be recovered from the franchisee in addition to without prejudice to any other remedies and rights</li><li>The franchisee, its employees, agents and representatives shall provide services as an independent "entity" on an exclusive basis and nothing contained herein shall be deemed to create any partnership, joint venture, employment or relationship of principal and agent between the parties hereto or between the Achanumber.com and the franchisee's representatives and employees are to provide the franchisee with any right, power or authority, whether express or implied to create any such duty or obligation.</li><li>The franchisee may publish advertisement in newspapers at his own cost with the prior approval from the COMPANY for text matter and design.</li><li>The franchisee will not be allowed without permission to make any alteration/ correction in the text matter of forms, e-mails or any printed materials supplied by the .</li><li>The terms and conditions may be amended as and when any changes, addition or deletion is required with the consent of both the parties except what is stated herein above..</li><li>The franchisee is not authorized to assign or otherwise transfer the benefits of this agreement or part thereof to a third party.</li><li>The fix Commission ratio of the franchisee will be decided time to time by AchaNumber.com</li><li>Governing Language and Law: The language to